io.spine.protobuf

Class TypeConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.spine.protobuf.TypeConverter

  • @Internal
public final class TypeConverter
extends java.lang.Object
    A utility for converting the Protobuf Messages (in form of Any) into arbitrary Java Objects and vice versa.

    Currently, the supported types are the following:

    • Message - converted via AnyPacker.
    • Java primitives - the passed Any is unpacked into one of the types Int32Value, Int64Value, UInt32Value, UInt64Value, FloatValue, DoubleValue, BoolValue, StringValue, BytesValue and then transformed into the corresponding Java type, either a primitive value, or String of ByteString. For more info, see the official document.
    • Java Enum types - the passed Any is unpacked into the EnumValue type and then is converted to the Java Enum through the value name or number.
